Test Name: OAK (Osteoarthritis Kinase), IGE (Immunoglobulin E) and SERUM Protein Analysis
Purpose: To quantitatively analyze osteoarthritis kinase, immunoglobulin E, and serum protein levels for clinical diagnostic assessment.
Equipment: OAK/IGE/SERUM assay kits, calibrated pipettes, microplates, plate reader/spectrophotometer, microcentrifuge, incubator/water bath, refractometer
